rport|Chicago\u2013O'Hare]], [[Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky International Airport|Cincinnati]], [[Cleveland Hopkins International Airport|Cleveland]], [[John Glenn Columbus International Airport|Columbus\u2013Glenn]], [[Dallas/Fort Worth International Airport|Dallas/Fort Worth]], [[Detroit Metropolitan Airport|Detroit]], [[Bradley International Airport|Hartford]], [[Indianapolis International Airport|Indianapolis]], [[Kansas City International Airport|Kansas City]], [[Kingston Norman Rogers Airport|Kingston (ON)]], [[London International Airport|London (ON)]], [[Memphis International Airport|Memphis]], [[Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport|Milwaukee]], [[Minneapolis\u2013Saint Paul International Airport|Minneapolis/St. Paul]], [[Montr\u00e9al\u2013Trudeau International Airport|Montr\u00e9al\u2013Trudeau]], [[Nashville International Airport|Nashville]], [[Newark Liberty International Airport|Newark]], [[Louis Armstrong New Orleans International Airport|New Orleans]], [[North Bay/Jack Garland Airport|North Bay]], [[Philadelphia International Airport|Philadelphia]], [[Pittsburgh International Airport|Pittsburgh]], [[Raleigh\u2013Durham International Airport|Raleigh/Durham]], [[St. Louis Lambert International Airport|St. Louis]], [[Saint John Airport|Saint John (NB)]] (ends April 30, 2020),<ref name=\"ACsaintjohn\">{{cite web|url=https://aircanada.mediaroom.com/2019-07-03-Air-Canada-Announces-Increased-Capacity-and-Enhanced-Services-to-Atlantic-Canada|title=Air Canada Announces Increased Capacity and Enhanced Services to Atlantic Canada|publisher=Air Canada|date=July 3, 2019|access-date=July 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703171243/https://aircanada.mediaroom.com/2019-07-03-Air-Canada-Announces-Increased-Capacity-and-Enhanced-Services-to-Atlantic-Canada|archive-date=July 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Sarnia Chris Hadfield Airport|Sarnia]] (ends July 26, 2020),<ref>https://blackburnnews.com/sarnia/sarnia-news/2020/03/26/air-canada-grounding