rport|Newark]], [[Louis Armstrong New Orleans International Airport|New Orleans]], [[North Bay/Jack Garland Airport|North Bay]], [[Philadelphia International Airport|Philadelphia]], [[Pittsburgh International Airport|Pittsburgh]], [[Raleigh\u2013Durham International Airport|Raleigh/Durham]], [[St. Louis Lambert International Airport|St. Louis]], [[Saint John Airport|Saint John (NB)]] (ends April 30, 2020),<ref name=\"ACsaintjohn\">{{cite web|url=https://aircanada.mediaroom.com/2019-07-03-Air-Canada-Announces-Increased-Capacity-and-Enhanced-Services-to-Atlantic-Canada|title=Air Canada Announces Increased Capacity and Enhanced Services to Atlantic Canada|publisher=Air Canada|date=July 3, 2019|access-date=July 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703171243/https://aircanada.mediaroom.com/2019-07-03-Air-Canada-Announces-Increased-Capacity-and-Enhanced-Services-to-Atlantic-Canada|archive-date=July 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Sarnia Chris Hadfield Airport|Sarnia]] (ends July 26, 2020)<ref>https://blackburnnews.com/sarnia/sarnia-news/2020/03/26/air-canada-grounding-flights-sarnia-good/</ref>, [[Sault Ste. Marie Airport|Sault Ste. Marie (ON)]], [[Sudbury Airport|Sudbury]], [[JA Douglas McCurdy Sydney Airport|Sydney (NS)]], [[Timmins/Victor M. Power Airport|Timmins]], [[Washington Dulles International Airport|Washington\u2013Dulles]], [[Reagan National Airport|Washington\u2013National]], [[Windsor International Airport|Windsor]]<br />'''Seasonal:''' [[Gander International Airport|Gander]], [[Mont Tremblant International Airport|Mont Tremblant]], [[T. F. Green Airport|Providence (RI)]], [[Savannah/Hilton Head International Airport|Savannah]] | <ref name=\"Air Canada Flight Schedules\"/>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Air Canada Rouge]] | [[Grantley Adams International Airport|Barbados]], [[El Dorado International Airport|Bogot\u00e1]], [[Calgary International Airport|Calgary]], [[Canc\u00fan International Airport|Canc\u00fan]], [[Jardines del Rey Airport|Cayo Coco]], [[